) fails for cabinet roles. Link is permanently marked as accepted. Next visit hits 'already_accepted' branch and redirects to /partnerhome, but user_role was never set. User is stuck.\nPATCH: Roll back StaffAccessLink on updateMe failure for cabinet roles:\n\\`\\`\\`js\n} catch (updateErr) {\n    console.error('Failed to update user role:', updateErr);\n    if (isCabinetRole) {\n        try {\n            await base44.entities.StaffAccessLink.update(link.id, {\n                invited_user: null,\n                invite_accepted_at: null\n            });\n        } catch (_) { /* ignore rollback failure */ }\n        setStatus('error');\n        setError(t('acceptinvite.error.cabinet_setup_failed'));\n        return;\n    }\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**P1: No concurrency guard on processInvite (line 338 retry button + useEffect)**\nRate-limit retry button calls processInvite without guard. Multiple concurrent executions possible.\nPATCH: Add useRef guard:\n\\`\\`\\`js\nconst isProcessingRef = React.useRef(false);\nasync function processInvite() {\n    if (isProcessingRef.current) return;\n    isProcessingRef.current = true;\n    try { /* ... */ } catch (err) { /* ... */ } finally { isProcessingRef.current = false; }\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**P1: handleLogoutAndRetry uses window.location.href = window.location.href (line 216)**\nUnreliable across browsers (Firefox may not reload).\nPATCH: Replace with window.location.reload()\n\n**P1: setTimeout redirects not cleared on unmount (lines 115, 127, 197)**\nStale redirects fire after component unmounts.\nPATCH: Store in useRef, clear in useEffect cleanup.\n\n**P1: isRateLimitError string-only detection (lines 13-17)**\nMisses structured 429 responses, false positive risk.\nPATCH: Check error.status === 429 first, then fall back to string match.\n\n**P1: Raw backend err.message rendered to user (line 208)**\nerr.message bypasses i18n, may show technical error text.\nPATCH: Always use t('acceptinvite.error.generic'), log raw error to console only.\n\n**P2: console.error in production (lines 180, 202)**\nLeaks internal error details.\nPATCH: Remove both.\n\n**P2: No client-side token verification after filter (line 86-93)**\nDefense-in-depth: verify link.token === token after fetch.\nPATCH: Add if (link.token !== token) { setStatus('invalid_token'); return; }\n\n**P2: Magic numbers for delays (lines 117, 129, 199, 215, 338)**\nUnnamed numeric constants scattered through code.\nPATCH: Extract to named constants.\n\n**P3: Decorative icons missing aria-hidden (multiple lines)**\nScreen readers announce decorative icons.\nPATCH: Add aria-hidden='true' to all decorative icons.\n\" 2>&1","timeout":180000,"description":"Run Codex independent review of acceptinvite.jsx"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01SHRjvUQZHdd3TFkP6MQBfM","tool_input":{"command":"cat acceptinvite.jsx > /tmp/acceptinvite_code.txt","description":"Copy file content to temp for Codex prompt"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DMiW1Dqp47bjgtBDH9FnAD","tool_input":{"command":"cat acceptinvite.jsx > codex_input.txt","description":"Copy file content to temp file for Codex prompt"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_011EcviZzpCYnHKaarpzH44b","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/ASUS/OneDrive/002 Menu/Claude AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/acceptinvite/codex_prompt.txt","content":"You are an independent code reviewer for a React/Base44 restaurant app (MenuApp).\n\nRULES TO CHECK:\n- usePartnerAccess() must only be inside <PartnerShell> wrapper\n- ALL user-facing strings must use t('key') from useI18n, key format: page.section.element\n- No hardcoded fallbacks like || 'Error'\n- No conditional React hooks\n- dangerouslySetInnerHTML needs sanitization (XSS risk)\n- Every createObjectURL needs revokeObjectURL\n- No console.log in production\n\nYOUR TASK:\n1. Read the code in acceptinvite.jsx (367 lines — staff invitation acceptance page)\n2. Read Claude's findings AND proposed patches below\n3. For each patch: APPROVE, 