il bypass), error handling gaps (partial state when StaffAccessLink.update succeeds but updateMe fails), race conditions (no abort controller in useEffect, retry button with no guard), React anti-patterns (missing useEffect cleanup, stale setTimeout), and i18n violations (raw err.message rendered to user). For each real issue found, provide priority P0-P3, line numbers, symptom, root cause, and proposed fix. Skip style-only nitpicks.\"","timeout":180000,"description":"Run Codex CLI to independently review acceptinvite code"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EkkgfXmzZdVNFVMYUGi9PY","tool_input":{"command":"codex exec \"Review pages/acceptinvite/acceptinvite.jsx (367 lines). Staff invitation acceptance page for React/Base44 restaurant app. Focus on: security (token handling, role escalation, email bypass), error handling (partial state when StaffAccessLink.update succeeds but updateMe fails), race conditions (no abort in useEffect, retry button no guard), React anti-patterns (missing cleanup, stale setTimeout), i18n (raw err.message to user). For each issue: priority P0-P3, line numbers, symptom, root cause, proposed fix. Skip style nitpicks.\"","timeout":180000,"description":"Codex independent review of acceptinvite"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01WaEAeB1MpLeUuirHh98vEk","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx && git commit -m \"add acceptinvite for initial review\"","description":"Stage and commit acceptinvite for initial review"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AJDxUWeYMZyvCUXeUV58sJ","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx && git commit -m \"add acceptinvite for initial review\"","description":"Git add and commit acceptinvite.jsx"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_012aYRqN9boSs3r5uFscbhZn","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx","description":"Git add acceptinvite.jsx"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01SrBXsVT27bwyH6x6vGtJCt","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx","description":"Stage acceptinvite.jsx"}},{"tool_name":"AskUserQuestion","tool_use_id":"toolu_01FY1DUF7TQzTkeXjMvS9PqM","tool_input":{"questions":[{"question":"Git and file write commands keep getting blocked by permissions. Can you approve the pending permission prompts (or adjust your permission settings to allow git and file writes in this directory)?","header":"Permissions","options":[{"label":"I'll approve now","description":"I see the permission prompts and will approve them"},{"label":"Check settings","description":"I need to check my Claude Code permission settings first"}],"multiSelect":false}]}},{"tool_name":"AskUserQuestion","tool_use_id":"toolu_01WD7jQfmxNRYkRP9H2z2wjC","tool_input":{"questions":[{"question":"Git and file write commands keep getting blocked by permissions. Can you approve the pending permission prompts or adjust your permission settings to allow git and file writes in this directory?","header":"Permissions","options":[{"label":"I'll approve now","description":"I see the permission prompts and will approve them"},{"label":"Check settings","description":"I need to check my Claude Code permission settings first"}],"multiSelect":false}]}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VrjESKaDCmER4J93SpZVwo","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx","description":"Stage acceptinvite.jsx for commit"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dcve9EDrU3VDiWjMuK3qqT","tool_input":{"command":"git add acceptinvite.jsx","description":"git add acceptinvite.jsx"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Aor2FjjngZbqodHDh62DFv","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/ASUS/OneDrive/002 Menu/Claude AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/acceptinvite/acceptinvite.jsx","content":"import React, { useEffect, useState, useRef, useCallback } from 'react';\nimport { useSearchParams } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport { base44 } from '@/api/base44Client';\nimport { Loader2, CheckCircle, XCircle, AlertCircle, Mail, AlertTriangle, RefreshCcw } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { Button } from \"@/components/ui/button\";\nimport { Card, CardContent } from \"@/components/ui/card\";\nimport { useI18n } from \"@/components/i18n\";\n\n// ============================================================\n// HELPERS\n// ============================================================\n\n// BUG-AI-001 fix: check structured status code first, then string fallback\nfunction isRateLimitError(error) {\n  if (!error) return false;\n  if (error.status === 429 || error.statusCode === 429 || error.code === 429) return true;\n  const msg = (error.message || error.toString() || \"\").toLowerCase();\n  return msg.includes(\"rate limit\") || msg.includes(\"too many requests\");\n}\n\n// LOCKED DM-027: Role mapping StaffAccessLink.staff_role → User.user_role\n// Note: 'partner_manager' as staff_role = \"старший официант\" (senior staff)\n// This is NOT the same as User.user_role='partner_manager' (управляющий)\nfunction mapStaffRoleToUserRole(staffRole) {\n    const mapping = {\n        'director': 'partner_owner',\n        'managing_director': 'partner_manager',\n        'partner_manager': 'partner_staff',  // senior staff → staff page\n        'partner_staff': 'partner_staff',\n        'kitchen': 'kitchen'\n    };\n    return mapping[staffRole] || 'partner_staff';\n}\n\n// LOCKED DM-027: Roles with cabinet access\nfunction hasCabinetAccess(staffRole) {\n    return ['director', 'managing_director'].includes(staffRole);\n}\n\n// Retry helper with delay\nasync function retryAsync(fn, maxRetries = 2, delayMs = 500) {\n    let lastError;\n    for (let i = 0; i <= maxRetries; i++) {\n        try {\n            return await fn();\n        } catch (err) {\n            lastError = err;\n            if (i < maxRetries) {\n                await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delayMs));\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    throw lastError;\n}\n\n// BUG-AI-005 fix: named constants for redirect delays\nconst REDIRECT_DELAY_MS = 2000;\nconst REDIRECT_DELAY_SHORT_MS = 1500;\nconst LOGOUT_DELAY_MS = 500;\nconst RETRY_DEBOUNCE_MS = 100;\n\n// ============================================================\n// MAIN COMPONENT\n// ============================================================\n\nexport default function AcceptInvitePage() {\n    const { t } = useI18n();\n    const [searchParams] = useSearchParams();\n    const token = searchParams.get('token');\n    const [status, setStatus] = useState('loading');\n    const [error, setError] = useState(null);\n    const [linkData, setLinkData] = useState(null);\n    const [currentUser, setCurrentUser] = useState(null);\n\n    // BUG-AI-002 fix: concurrency guard\n    const isProcessingRef = useRef(false);\n    // BUG-AI-004 fix: track setTimeout for cleanup on unmount\n    const redirectTimerRef = useRef(null);\n\n    // BUG-AI-004 fix: clear redirect timer on unmount\n    useEffect(() => {\n        return () => {\n            if (redirectTimerRef.current) clearTimeout(redirectTimerRef.current);\n        };\n    }, []);\n\n    // Get redirect URL based on role (LOCKED DM-027)\n    function getRedirectUrl(link) {\n        if (hasCabinetAccess(link.staff_role)) {\n            return '/partnerhome';  // Cabinet access - no token needed\n        }\n        return `/staffordersmobile?token=${token}`;  // Staff - token access\n    }\n\n    // Schedule redirect with cleanup tracking\n    function scheduleRedirect(url, delayMs) {\n        redirectTimerRef.current = setTimeout(() => {\n            window.location.href = url;\n        }, delayMs);\n    }\n\n    const processInvite = useCallback(async () => {\n        // BUG-AI-002 fix: prevent double execution\n        if (isProcessingRef.current) return;\n        isProcessingRef.current = true;\n\n        try {\n            setStatus('loading');\n            const links = await base44.entities.StaffAccessLink.filter({ token });\n\n            if (!links || links.length === 0) {\n                setStatus('invalid_token');\n                return;\n            }\n\n            const link = links[0];\n\n            // BUG-AI-006 fix: defense-in-depth client-side token verification\n            if (link.token !== token) {\n                setStatus('invalid_token');\n                return;\n            }\n\n            setLinkData(link);\n\n            if (!link.is_active) {\n                setStatus('error');\n                setError(t('acceptinvite.link_disabled'));\n                return;\n            }\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // BRANCH: No email required (link-only access)\n            // ============================================================\n            if (!link.invite_email) {\n                // P0 SEC: Д/УД БЕЗ email = ошибка (нужен email для доступа к кабинету)\n                if (hasCabinetAccess(link.staff_role)) {\n                    setStatus('error');\n                    setError(t('acceptinvite.error.email_required_for_cabinet'));\n                    return;\n                }\n\n                setStatus('no_email_required');\n                const redirectUrl = getRedirectUrl(link);\n                scheduleRedirect(redirectUrl, REDIRECT_DELAY_SHORT_MS);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // BRANCH: Already accepted\n            // ============================================================\n            if (link.invite_accepted_at && link.invited_user) {\n                setStatus('already_accepted');\n                const redirectUrl = getRedirectUrl(link);\n                scheduleRedirect(redirectUrl, REDIRECT_DELAY_MS);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // Check auth\n            // ============================================================\n            setStatus('checking');\n            const isAuthenticated = await base44.auth.isAuthenticated();\n\n            if (!isAuthenticated) {\n                const currentUrl = window.location.href;\n                base44.auth.redirectToLogin(currentUrl);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            const user = await base44.auth.me();\n            setCurrentUser(user);\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // Verify email match\n            // ============================================================\n            const userEmail = (user.email || '').toLowerCase().trim();\n            const inviteEmail = (link.invite_email || '').toLowerCase().trim();\n\n            if (userEmail !== inviteEmail) {\n                setStatus('email_mismatch');\n                return;\n            }\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // Accept invitation\n            // ============================================================\n            await base44.entities.StaffAccessLink.update(link.id, {\n                invited_user: user.id,\n                invite_accepted_at: new Date().toISOString()\n            });\n\n            // Set user role and partner (with retry for cabinet roles)\n            const userRole = mapStaffRoleToUserRole(link.staff_role);\n            const isCabinetRole = hasCabinetAccess(link.staff_role);\n\n            try {\n                // SEC-020: Retry updateMe for reliability\n                await retryAsync(async () => {\n                    await base44.auth.updateMe({\n                        user_role: userRole,\n                        partner: link.partner\n                    });\n                }, 2, 500);\n            } catch (updateErr) {\n                // SEC-020: For cabinet roles, updateMe failure is critical\n                if (isCabinetRole) {\n                    // BUG-AI-003 fix: rollback StaffAccessLink to allow retry\n                    try {\n                        await base44.entities.StaffAccessLink.update(link.id, {\n                            invited_user: null,\n                            invite_accepted_at: null\n                        });\n                    } catch (_) { /* ignore rollback failure */ }\n                    setStatus('error');\n                    setError(t('acceptinvite.error.cabinet_setup_failed'));\n                    return;  // Do NOT redirect\n                }\n                // For staff roles, continue with token access as fallback\n            }\n\n            // ============================================================\n            // Success - redirect\n            // ============================================================\n            setStatus('success');\n            const redirectUrl = getRedirectUrl(link);\n            scheduleRedirect(redirectUrl, REDIRECT_DELAY_MS);\n\n        } catch (err) {\n            if (isRateLimitError(err)) {\n                setStatus('rate_limit');\n                return;\n            }\n            setStatus('error');\n            // BUG-AI-007 fix: never render raw err.message to user\n            setError(t('acceptinvite.error.generic'));\n        } finally {\n            isProcessingRef.current = false;\n        }\n    }, [token, t]);\n\n    useEffect(() => {\n        if (!token) {\n            setStatus('no_token');\n            return;\n        }\n        processInvite();\n    }, [token, processInvite]);\n\n    function handleLogoutAndRetry() {\n        base44.auth.logout();\n        // BUG-AI-008 fix: use reload() instead of self-assignment (unreliable in Firefox)\n        setTimeout(() => {\n            window.location.reload();\n        }, LOGOUT_DELAY_MS);\n    }\n\n    return (\n        <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-slate-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4\">\n            <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n                <CardContent className=\"pt-6\">\n\n                    {/* Loading / Checking */}\n                    {(status === 'loading' || status === 'checking') && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <Loader2 className=\"w-12 h-12 animate-spin text-indigo-600 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600\">\n                                {status === 'loading'\n                                    ? t('acceptinvite.loading')\n                                    : t('acceptinvite.checking_auth')}\n                            </p>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Success */}\n                    {status === 'success' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <CheckCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-green-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.success.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.success.message')}\n                            </p>\n                            <Loader2 className=\"w-5 h-5 animate-spin text-slate-400 mx-auto\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Already Accepted */}\n                    {status === 'already_accepted' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <CheckCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-green-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.already_accepted.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.already_accepted.message')}\n                            </p>\n                            <Loader2 className=\"w-5 h-5 animate-spin text-slate-400 mx-auto\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* No Email Required */}\n                    {status === 'no_email_required' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <CheckCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-blue-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.no_email_required.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.no_email_required.message')}\n                            </p>\n                            <Loader2 className=\"w-5 h-5 animate-spin text-slate-400 mx-auto\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* No Token */}\n                    {status === 'no_token' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <XCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-red-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.no_token.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.no_token.message')}\n                            </p>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Invalid Token */}\n                    {status === 'invalid_token' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <XCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-red-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.invalid_token.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.invalid_token.message')}\n                            </p>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Email Mismatch */}\n                    {status === 'email_mismatch' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <AlertCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-amber-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.email_mismatch.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.email_mismatch.message', {\n                                    currentEmail: currentUser?.email,\n                                    inviteEmail: linkData?.invite_email\n                                })}\n                            </p>\n                            <Button onClick={handleLogoutAndRetry} className=\"w-full\">\n                                <Mail className=\"w-4 h-4 mr-2\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                                {t('acceptinvite.email_mismatch.button')}\n                            </Button>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Rate Limit */}\n                    {status === 'rate_limit' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <div className=\"w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full bg-amber-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n                                <AlertTriangle className=\"w-8 h-8 text-amber-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            </div>\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.rate_limit.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.rate_limit.message')}\n                            </p>\n                            <Button\n                                onClick={() => { setStatus('loading'); setTimeout(processInvite, RETRY_DEBOUNCE_MS); }}\n                                className=\"w-full bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700\"\n                            >\n                                <RefreshCcw className=\"w-4 h-4 mr-2\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                                {t('common.retry')}\n                            </Button>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Error */}\n                    {status === 'error' && (\n                        <div className=\"text-center py-8\">\n                            <XCircle className=\"w-16 h-16 text-red-500 mx-auto mb-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n                            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">\n                                {t('acceptinvite.error.title')}\n                            </h2>\n                            <p className=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">\n                                {error || t('acceptinvite.error.generic')}\n                            </p>\n                            <Button variant=\"outline\" onClick={() => window.location.reload()}>\n                                {t('common.retry')}\n                            </Button>\n                        </div>\n                    )}\n\n                </CardContent>\n            </Card>\n        </div>\n    );\n}\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_014Zv5hbV6baDPQm3F8kzuAY","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/